Comparing safety:
- Raw pointers have risk of memory leaks if destructor is not implemented correctly, while smart pointers automatically clean up memory.
- Raw pointers can lead to double deletes if copy constructor and assignment operator are not implemented correctly, while smart pointers prevent this
- Raw pointers can lead to use after free if not handled

Comparing complexity:
